.TH "__radix_tree_replace" 9 "__radix_tree_replace" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__radix_tree_replace \- replace item in a slot
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __radix_tree_replace
.BI "(struct radix_tree_root *root "  ","
.BI "struct radix_tree_node *node "  ","
.BI "void __rcu **slot "  ","
.BI "void *item "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "root" 12
radix tree root
.IP "node" 12
pointer to tree node
.IP "slot" 12
pointer to slot in \fInode\fP
.IP "item" 12
new item to store in the slot.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For use with \fB__radix_tree_lookup\fP.  Caller must hold tree write locked
across slot lookup and replacement.
